cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about a machine learning approach to Tibetan word segmentation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on NLP and related topics. The use of a neural network classifier also suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a likely sub-category. Additionally, the use of subword units and the BPE algorithm suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) may be a relevant sub-category. The use of a decoding step and evaluation of F-score also suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) may be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the use of a baseline system and evaluation of performance gain suggests that cs.IR (Information Retrieval) may be a relevant sub-category.
